<subSubSection id="C30565347369AB2CFF5CFA61D5BF91A6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA036BF7369AB2CFF5CFA61D5BF91A6" blockId="1.[151,1437,1445,1974]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFF5CFA61D659901C" bold="true" box="[197,324,1522,1548]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Remarks:</emphasis>
The detailed description of the life cycle and development of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFBDAFA60D278901C" box="[1091,1381,1523,1548]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFBDAFA60D278901C" box="[1091,1381,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hydrodroma despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B4E7369AB2CFED9F98AD6F19023" author="Meyer" box="[320,492,1561,1587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refString="Meyer, E. (1985) Der Entwicklungszyklus von Hydrodroma despiciens (O. F. Muller 1776) (Acari. Hydrodromidae). Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement 66, 3, 321 - 453." type="journal article" year="1985">
Meyer (
<number id="3DD724987369AB2CFE3BF98AD6FE9023" box="[418,483,1561,1587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
immediately before 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B4E7369AB2CFD69F98AD48F9023" author="Wiles" box="[752,914,1561,1587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" refString="Wiles, P. R. (1985) The systematics of the British Hydrodromidae Viets, 1936. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement 70 (3), 365 - 403." type="journal article" year="1985">
Wiles (
<number id="3DD724987369AB2CFCD0F98AD4979023" box="[841,906,1561,1587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
cleared up the taxonomic situation of the European (sub)species of the genus. In a later paper, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B4E7369AB2CFC9AF9D3D4B8904A" author="Meyer" box="[771,933,1600,1626]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refString="Meyer, E. (1989) Comparative studies on the biology of water mites of the genus Hydrodroma (Actinedida: Hydrodromidae). In: Channabasawanna, G. P. &amp; Viraktamath, C. A. (eds.), Progress in Acarology Vol 1. Oxford and IBH Publ. Co, New Dehli, pp. 433 - 440." type="journal article" year="1989">
Meyer (
<number id="3DD724987369AB2CFCC6F9D3D481904A" box="[863,924,1600,1626]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the population on which her study was based, represented 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFE61F9F4D47C9090" box="[504,865,1639,1664]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="despiciens" subSpecies="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFE61F9F4D47C9090" box="[504,865,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hydrodroma despiciens pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a subspecies raised to species rank by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B4E7369AB2CFAA3F9F5D7F490B7" author="Gerecke" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" refString="Gerecke, R. (1991) Taxonomische, faunistische und okologische Untersuchungen an Wassermilben aus Sizilien unter Berucksichtigung anderer aquatischer Invertebraten. Lauterbornia, 7, 1 - 304." type="journal article" year="1991">
Gerecke (
<number id="3DD724987369AB2CFF39F91ED7FD90B7" box="[160,224,1677,1703]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. A revision of both slide material from Meyer's PhD thesis and newly collected populations confirms that exclusively 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFEC7F927D55790DD" box="[350,586,1716,1741]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFEC7F927D55790DD" box="[350,586,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hydrodroma pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was, and still is, present in the Mindelsee. In the course of this study, further characters were detected that separate 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFD22F948D43490E4" box="[699,809,1755,1780]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFD22F948D43490E4" box="[699,809,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFCEBF948D30F90E4" box="[882,1042,1755,1780]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFCEBF948D30F90E4" box="[882,1042,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: Integument papillae are sharply pointed (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFE86F892D6A3910A" box="[287,446,1793,1818]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFE86F892D6A3910A" box="[287,446,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
apically rounded) and more acetabula 
<number id="3DD724987369AB2CFC10F892D4B2910B" box="[905,943,1793,1819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6-8</number>
(in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFC79F892D363910A" box="[992,1150,1793,1818]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFC79F892D363910A" box="[992,1150,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<number id="3DD724987369AB2CFB1FF892D3B3910B" box="[1158,1198,1793,1819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4-6</number>
) lie in parallel rows where the genital flaps have their maximum width. These differences show that the two taxa should be considered separate species. Information so far published on the biology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFB8AF8DCD2379178" box="[1043,1322,1871,1896]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFB8AF8DCD2379178" box="[1043,1322,1871,1896]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hydrodroma despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, might in reality refer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFEDCF8E6D6AD919E" box="[325,432,1909,1934]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFEDCF8E6D6AD919E" box="[325,432,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or cannot be interpreted with certainty. Consequently, with regard to its life cycle, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D3C7369AB2CFAE6F8E6D60C91A5" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="B96BEAAD7369AB2CFAE6F8E6D60C91A5" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still a mostly unknown species.
</paragraph>
